            <div type="letter">
                <div type="text">
                    <opener>
                        <placeName>Down, Beckenham, Kent, | Railway Station, Orpington, S.E.R.</placeName>
                        <date>January 4, 1877</date>
                        <salute>Dear Sir,—</salute>
                    </opener>
                    <div type="transcription">
                        <p>My father directs me to thank you for your account of the alleged discovery in New Ireland.<ref target="#foot.f1"/> My father does not believe in the existence of the tailed men, but even if it should prove true it would (as a mere inherited monstrosity) have no important bearing on evolution.</p>
                        <p>Yours faithfully, <hi rend="smallCaps">Francis Darwin.</hi></p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                
                
                
            </div>
           
           
           <div type="footnotes">
                <note xml:id="foot.f1">An article on a report of tailed men at Kalili, New Ireland (now Kalil in Papua New Guinea) appeared in the <hi rend="italic">Auckland Star</hi>, 10 November 1876, p. 2. See also <hi rend="italic">Correspondence</hi> vol. 25, <ref target="./DCP-LETT-10764.xml">letter from Arthur Mellersh, 1 January 1877</ref>.</note>
                </div>
        
